<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1450" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1450">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/469.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Willard</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-27">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7. Minister of State requests me to inform you of contents of
                                telegram received last night from Spanish Minister, Mexico City,
                                Bouquet: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>Notwithstanding absolute guaranties repeatedly given by the
                                        chief of the Zapata forces, various Spaniards have been
                                        assassinated, many houses sacked and frequent robberies in
                                        the streets, there being a total absence of energetic action
                                        on part of authorities which change from day to day. For the
                                        moment there are no persons to whom to apply for
                                        protection.</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>